UID:38034-1793959200-1794157200@ccs-houston.com
SUMMARY:CCS $50\,000 Riftbound Invitational
DESCRIPTION:CCS $50\,000 Riftbound Invitational – 2026 Series Overview\nThe CCS $50\,000 Riftbound Invitational is a year-long competitive circuit for Riftbound players. \nThe season concludes on November 6–8\, 2026 in Houston\, Texas\, with a $50\,000 Invite-Only Championship featuring 128 of the best players in the game. \nGo to the Topdeck Invitational Page \n\nHow to Qualify for the $50\,000 Invitational\n3 Ways to Qualify (128 Total Spots)\n1. Auto-Qualify – Top 8 from each $25K Main Event (6 events) \nTotal Spots: 48 \n2. Points Leaderboard – Top performers across all events \nTotal Spots: 64 \n3. LCQ Winners – Winner of each Last Chance Qualifier (16 events) \nTotal Spots: 16 \nIf a player qualifies through multiple methods\, leaderboard spots roll down to the next eligible player. \n\nBonus for the Most Consistent Players\nThe Top 8 players on the final Points Leaderboard earn a Round 1 Bye at the Invitational. \n\nMain Qualifier Weekends – Structure & Prizes\nEach of the 6 qualifier weekends includes: \nSaturday – $25\,000 Main Event\n\nFormat: Standard\nSwiss + Top Cut\nTop 8 auto-qualify\nTop 128 placements earn leaderboard points\n\nSunday – $5\,000 Side Event\n\nOne-day event\nTop 8 earn 30 leaderboard points\nNo auto-invite\n\n\nLeaderboard Points System\nSaturday $25K Main Events (Top 128 Earn Points)\n1st — 100 \n2nd — 80 \n3rd–4th — 65 \n5th–8th — 50 \n9th–16th — 35 \n17th–32nd — 20 \n33rd–64th — 10 \n65th–128th — 5 \nTotal Points per Main Event: 1\,750 \nTotal Across All 6: 10\,500 \nSunday $5K Side Events — Points\nTop 8 — 30 points each \n\nLast Chance Qualifiers (LCQs)\n\n16 total events\nWinner of each LCQ earns an automatic invite\nOpen entry — no prior points required\n\n\nMain Qualifier Tournament Weekends\n(All 6 Events + Signup Links) \nQualifier Weekend 1\nJanuary 31 – February 1\, 2026 \n📍 Houston\, Texas \nSignup: https://topdeck.gg/event/25000-houston-invitational-qualifier-1 \nQualifier Weekend 2\nMarch 14–15\, 2026 \n📍 Houston\, Texas \nSignup: https://topdeck.gg/event/25000-houston-invitational-qualifier-2 \nQualifier Weekend 3\nMay 23–24\, 2026 \n📍 Atlanta\, Georgia \nSignup: https://topdeck.gg/event/25000-houston-invitational-qualifier-3 \nQualifier Weekend 4\nJuly 11–12\, 2026 \n📍 Atlanta\, Georgia \nSignup: https://topdeck.gg/event/25000-atlanta-invitational-qualifier-4 \nQualifier Weekend 5\nSeptember 19–20\, 2026 \n📍 Houston\, Texas \nSignup: https://topdeck.gg/event/25000-houston-invitational-qualifier-5 \nQualifier Weekend 6\nOctober 10-11\, 2026 \n📍 Atlanta\, Georgia \nSignup: https://topdeck.gg/event/25000-atlanta-invitational-qualifier-6 \n\nCCS $50\,000 Riftbound Invitational Championship Weekend\nNovember 6–8\, 2026 \n📍 Houston\, Texas \n128 players compete for $50\,000 and the title of CCS Riftbound Champion.
URL:https://ccs-houston.com/events/ccs-50000-riftbound-invitational/
CATEGORIES:Trading Card Game
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://ccs-houston.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Riftbound-50K-Invitational-Banner-IG-1.png
END:VEVENT
